Description: Twenty-eight fragments of a papyrus roll with Coptic text on front and back, written along and against the fibres respectively. There are also a few small blank fragments. 2 principal groups of fragments with several others. Traces of another script (?) in thicker pen on two of the fragments.The fragments are understood to be numbered in columns (top to bottom, left to right) as seen from the scanned image labelled as 'front'.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380793) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380793)
